  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-section">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>How long does it take to see results from LED face masks?</strong>
      <p>
        Most users see subtle improvements in skin texture and breakouts after 4–6 weeks of consistent use (3–5 times per week). More dramatic results—such as visible wrinkle reduction—appear around 8–12 weeks. Some users don't notice anything after 2 weeks; patience is essential.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Is the Wireless LED Red Light Face Mask safe for sensitive skin?</strong>
      <p>
        Yes, LED light therapy is generally safe for all skin types, including sensitive skin. However, if you have a compromised skin barrier, active rosacea, or are taking photosensitizing medications, consult a dermatologist first. Some users report mild dryness or redness initially; this usually resolves after a few sessions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Can I use the mask every day?</strong>
      <p>
        Yes, daily use is safe, but not necessary. The recommended frequency is 3–5 times per week for optimal results. Daily use won't dramatically speed up results and may increase the risk of minor side effects like dryness.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Do I need to use it with skincare products?</strong>
      <p>
        No, but light therapy works best with a consistent skincare routine. Use it on clean, dry skin, and continue with your regular moisturizer and sunscreen. Don't apply heavy creams or serums right before the mask (they block light penetration).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Is this mask FDA-cleared?</strong>
      <p>
        LED face masks are classified as cosmetic beauty devices, not medical devices, so they don't carry FDA clearance for treating skin conditions. However, clinical studies do show that red light therapy can improve acne and fine lines. This mask is safe but should not be marketed as a cure or treatment for medical conditions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>What's the difference between red light and other colors in the 7-color therapy?</strong>
      <p>
        <strong>Red light (600–700 nm):</strong> Anti-aging, collagen stimulation, wrinkles. <strong>Near-infrared (700–1100 nm):</strong> Deep penetration, skin renewal. <strong>Blue light:</strong> Acne-fighting (antibacterial). <strong>Green/Yellow:</strong> Soothing, reducing redness. Use red for anti-aging, blue for breakouts, or 7-color mode for general skin health.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>Can I use the mask with my other skincare devices (microneedler, etc.)?</strong>
      <p>
        Yes, but space them out. Don't use the LED mask immediately after microneedling (wait 24 hours to avoid irritation). Light therapy pairs well with treatments like serums and moisturizers but not with active exfoliants on the same day.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>How long is the USB-C charge and how often do I need to recharge?</strong>
      <p>
        The Wireless LED Red Light Face Mask holds a charge for approximately 15–20 uses. If you use it 4 times per week, you'll need to recharge once per week. The full charge takes about 2 hours via USB-C.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

